{"parse":{"title":"Mirror of the Polish Crown","pageid":14025210,"revid":853576341,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><p><b>Mirror of the Polish Crown</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Polish_language\" title=\"Polish language\">Polish</a>: <i><span lang=\"pl\">Zwierciad\u0142o Korony Polskiej</span></i>) (full title <i>Mirror of the Polish Crown expressing the profound insults and great anxieties it receives from the Jews</i>) is an antisemitic <a href=\"/wiki/Pamphlet\" title=\"Pamphlet\">pamphlet</a> published in 1618 by <a href=\"/wiki/Sebastian_Miczy%C5%84ski\" title=\"Sebastian Miczy\u0144ski\">Sebastian Miczy\u0144ski</a>, professor of philosophy at <a href=\"/wiki/Cracow\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Cracow\">Cracow</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Jagellonian_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jagellonian University\">Jagellonian University</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  Because this pamphlet was one of the causes of the anti-Jewish riots in Cracow, it was censored by <a href=\"/wiki/Sigismund_III_Vasa\" title=\"Sigismund III Vasa\">Sigismund III Vasa</a>. , further to a petition from local Jews to the Polish crown. Despite this, the book run through numerous reprints.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In this pamphlet Jews were accused with political treachery, robbery, swindling, murder, <a href=\"/wiki/Witchcraft\" title=\"Witchcraft\">witchcraft</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Sacrilege\" title=\"Sacrilege\">sacrilege</a>, however religious accusations are of secondary importance. The pamphlet mainly focuses on the economic activities of the Jews and advocates the expulsion of the Jews from Poland.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mirror_of_the_Polish_Crown&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Dubnow, S. M.; Dubnow, Simon; Friedlaender, Israel (2000). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=vL60sEf7OPoC&amp;pg=PA43&amp;lpg=PA43&amp;dq=Mirror+of+the+Polish+Crown&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=wmWzBOQQ7b&amp;sig=TSrZ-HjxDsxTaM0oNwRJUX-ZAMA&amp;hl=en&amp;ei=O2iiTaTxHo_EgAf2mL3aBQ&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;ct=result&amp;resnum=5&amp;ved=0CDoQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&amp;q=Mirror%20of%20the%20Polish%20Crown&amp;f=false\"><i>History of the Jews in Russia and Poland</i></a> (Reprint. ed.). Bergenfield, NJ: Avotaynu. p.&#160;43. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-886223-11-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-886223-11-0\">978-1-886223-11-0</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+the+Jews+in+Russia+and+Poland&amp;rft.place=Bergenfield%2C+NJ&amp;rft.pages=43&amp;rft.edition=Reprint.&amp;rft.pub=Avotaynu&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-886223-11-0&amp;rft.aulast=Dubnow&amp;rft.aufirst=S.+M.&amp;rft.au=Dubnow%2C+Simon&amp;rft.au=Friedlaender%2C+Israel&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DvL60sEf7OPoC%26pg%3DPA43%26lpg%3DPA43%26dq%3DMirror%2Bof%2Bthe%2BPolish%2BCrown%26source%3Dbl%26ots%3DwmWzBOQQ7b%26sig%3DTSrZ-HjxDsxTaM0oNwRJUX-ZAMA%26hl%3Den%26ei%3DO2iiTaTxHo_EgAf2mL3aBQ%26sa%3DX%26oi%3Dbook_result%26ct%3Dresult%26resn